text: Three on a Match is a 1932 American crime drama movie directed by Mervyn LeRoy and starring Joan Blondell, Bette Davis, Warren William, Ann Dvorak, Lyle Talbot, Humphrey Bogart, Edward Arnold. It was distributed by Warner Bros and was released to poor reviews. ==Other websites== * * * Category:1932 crime drama movies Category:American crime drama movies Category:Warner Bros. movies Category:Movies directed by Mervyn LeRoy Category:Movies set in the 1910s Category:Movies set in the 1920s
